===Etymology 1===
{{ja-kanjitab|おもて|yomi=k}}

Ultimately from {{inh|ja|ojp|sort=おもて|-}}. Cognate with {{m|ja|面|tr=omote||}}.<ref name="KDJ2-表">{{R:Nihon Kokugo Daijiten 2}}</ref> Derived as a compound of {{compound|ja|sort=おもて|面|tr1=omo|t1=[[face]]|手|tr2=te|t2=[[hand]]; [[direction]], [[side]]}}, basically meaning "face-wards; facing side".<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref><ref name="DDJS">{{R:Digital-Daijisen}}</ref><ref name="KDJ2-面">{{R:Nihon Kokugo Daijiten 2|面}}</ref><ref name="KDJ2-手">{{R:Nihon Kokugo Daijiten 2|手}}</ref><ref name="SMK5"/>

The term ''omote'' in general is attested since the ''{{w|Nihon Shoki}}'' of 720.<ref name="KDJ2-面"/> The {{m|ja||表}} spelling for this word is attested from roughly 1000.<ref name="KDJ2-表"/>

Cognate with {{cog|ryu|表|tr=umuti}}.

